<ul>
<li><em><b>Sections</b></em> are played one after another, <em>eg. Intro -> Verse -> Chorus -> Outro</em></li>
<li><em><b>Parts</b></em> (such as melodies, basslines, and drumbeats) are played together in a <em><b>Section</b></em>.</li>
</ul>

<hr>

        <p>The gallery contains <b>things</b> which are stored as text files (JSON). 
            Here are the different <b>types</b> of <b>things</b>:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Soundset</li>
            <li>Part</li>
            <ul>
                <li>Drumbeat</li>
                <li>Melody</li>
            </ul>
            <li>Section</li>
            <li>Song</li>
            <li>Playlist</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            A <b>Soundset</b> contains a list of URLs to audio samples.
        </p>
        <p>
            A <b>Part</b> describes when and how to play the samples in a <b>Soundset</b>. A <b>Part</b> is a <b>Drumbeat</b> or <b>Melody</b>
        </p>
        <p>
            A <b>Section</b> contains one or more <b>Parts</b> to be played simultaneously.
        </p>
        <p>
            A <b>Song</b> contains one or more <b>Sections</b> to be played one-after-another.
        </p>
        <p>
            A <b>Playlist</b> is, of course, a list of <b>Songs</b>.
        </p>

        <hr>

        <p><b>Things</b> posted to the gallery can be <b>remixed</b> by other users.

        <hr>

        <ul>
            <li>A <b>Soundset</b> can be created in the <a href="/soundset-editor.htm">Soundset Editor</a>.</li>
            <li>A <b>Playlist</b> can be created by pressing "Add To Playlist" while browsing the <a href="/">gallery</a>. </li>
            <li>The other <b>types</b> can be made in <a href="/create">OMG Create</a>.</li>
        </ul>
